headline: Assessing TE Connectivity (TEL) Valuation After Recent Share Price Pullback
summary: What TE Connectivity stock’s recent performance tells you TE Connectivity (TEL) shares have pulled back recently, with a 3.2% decline over the past day and a 7.1% move lower across the past week, following softer performance over the past month and past three months. For longer term holders, that comes after total returns of 51.3% over the past year, 87.6% over three years and 94.9% over five years, creating a different backdrop from the shorter term price moves.
